{# Mistral-native user prompt for mistral-small:24b. Ollama wraps this
   automatically into [INST] ... [/INST]. Style follows the model card
   ( https://huggingface.co/mistralai/Mistral-Small-24B-Instruct-2501 ):
   crisp task framing first, then payload, then a single bullet-list of
   binding constraints next to the assistant turn (recency-window pattern).
   Mistral 24B responds well to short, declarative constraint lists; long
   prose preambles tend to dilute instruction-following. #}
Task: write an abstractive summary of the following podcast episode transcript.

{% if title -%}
Episode title: {{ title }}

{% endif -%}
Transcript:
{{ transcript }}

Write a single coherent summary covering the episode's substantive content. Target length: {{ paragraphs_min }}–{{ paragraphs_max }} paragraphs.

Constraints (must hold):
- Abstractive and synthesized — paraphrase ideas in your own words; do not copy sentences verbatim.
- Focus on decisions, arguments, lessons, and insights that drove the episode forward.
- Exclude advertisements, sponsorships, listener mail, and housekeeping segments.
- Do not include speaker names. Do not include direct quotations.
- Do not introduce facts or claims that are not supported by the transcript.
- Plain text only — no markdown, no headings, no bullet lists, no code blocks, no JSON.
- Begin the response with the first sentence of the summary; no preamble such as "Here is the summary" or "Summary:".
- Separate paragraphs with a single blank line.
